ement of freedom as well as to realise social and distributive justice. He offers a powerful account of economic injustice and justice that is centered on his understanding of freedom and its conditions." Bruce Baum, "[J. S. Mill and Liberal Socialism]", Nadia Urbanati and Alex Zacharas, eds., <i id="mwB50">J.S. Mill's Political Thought: A Bicentennial Reassessment</i> (Cambridge: Cambridge University Press, 2007).</span></li><li about="#cite_note-56" id="cite_note-56"><a href="./Socialism#cite_ref-56" rel="mw:referencedBy"><span class="mw-linkback-text">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-56" class="mw-reference-text">Robert Gildea, "1848 in European Collective Memory", in Evans and Strandmann, eds. <i id="mwB54">The Revolutions in Europe, 1848–1849</i> pp. 207–35</span></li><li about="#cite_note-57" id="cite_note-57"><a href="./Socialism#cite_ref-57" rel="mw:referencedBy"><span class="mw-linkback-text">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-57" class="mw-reference-text">pp. 276–77, <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Alfred_Edward_Taylor" title="Alfred Edward Taylor" id="mwB58">A.E. Taylor</a>, <i id="mwB6A">Plato: The Man and His Work</i>, Dover 2001.</span></li><li about="#cite_note-58" id="cite_note-58"><a href="./Socialism#cite_ref-58" rel="mw:referencedBy"><span class="mw-linkback-text">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-58" class="mw-reference-text">p. 257, <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./W._D._Ross" title="W. D. Ross" id="mwB6E">W. D. Ross</a>, <i id="mwB6I">Aristotle</i>, 6th ed.</span></li><li about="#cite_note-59" id="cite_note-59"><a href="./Socialism#cite_ref-59" rel="mw:referencedBy"><span class="mw-linkback-text">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-59" class="mw-reference-text"><i id="mwB6M">A Short History of the World</i>. Progress Publishers. Moscow, 1974</span></li><li about="#cite_note-60" id="cite_note-60"><a href="./Socialism#cite_ref-60" rel="mw:referencedBy"><span class="mw-linkback-text">↑