yclopedia+Britannica&amp;rft.atitle=Guild+Socialism&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.britannica.com%2FEBchecked%2Ftopic%2F248652%2FGuild-Socialism&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ASocialism" class="Z3988" about="#mwt250" id="mwCCo"></span><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r879151008" about="#mwt250" typeof="mw:Extension/templatestyles" data-mw='{"name":"templatestyles","attrs":{"src":"Module:Citation/CS1/styles.css"},"body":{"extsrc":""}}' id="mwCCs"/></span></li><li about="#cite_note-93" id="cite_note-93"><a href="./Socialism#cite_ref-93" rel="mw:referencedBy"><span class="mw-linkback-text">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-93" class="mw-reference-text"><a rel="mw:ExtLink" class="external text" href="http://www.marxisthistory.org/subject/usa/eam/secondinternational.html" id="mwCCw"><i id="mwCC0">The Second (Socialist) International 1889–1923</i></a>. Retrieved 12 July 2007.</span></li><li about="#cite_note-Anarchism_1962_pp._263-94" id="cite_note-Anarchism_1962_pp._263-94"><span rel="mw:referencedBy"><a href="./Socialism#cite_ref-Anarchism_1962_pp._263_94-0"><span class="mw-linkback-text">1 </span></a><a href="./Socialism#cite_ref-Anarchism_1962_pp._263_94-1"><span class="mw-linkback-text">2 </span></a></span> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-Anarchism_1962_pp._263-94" class="mw-reference-text"><a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./George_Woodcock" title="George Woodcock" id="mwCC4">George Woodcock</a>. <i id="mwCC8">Anarchism: A History of Libertarian Ideas and Movements</i> (1962). pp. 263–64</span></li><li about="#cite_note-95" id="cite_note-95"><a href="./Socialism#cite_ref-95" rel="mw:referencedBy"><span class="mw-linkback-text">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-95" class="mw-reference-text">Marx, Engels, <i id="mwCDA">Communist Manifesto</i>, Selected Works, p. 52</span></li><li about="#cite_note-96" id="cite_note-96"><a href="./Socialism#cite_ref-96" rel="mw:referencedBy"><span class="m