mwDJ4">ISBN</a><span typeof="mw:Entity" id="mwDJ8"> </span><a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Special:BookSources/978-0-7425-0795-1" title="Special:BookSources/978-0-7425-0795-1" id="mwDKA">978-0-7425-0795-1</a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Philosophy+and+the+Problems+of+Work%3A+A+Reader&amp;rft.place=Lanham%2C+Md&amp;rft.pages=224&amp;rft.pub=Rowman+%26+Littlefield&amp;rft.date=2001&amp;rft.isbn=978-0-7425-0795-1&amp;rft.aulast=Schaff&amp;rft.aufirst=Kory&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ASocialism" class="Z3988" about="#mwt1338" id="mwDKE"></span><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r879151008" about="#mwt1338" typeof="mw:Extension/templatestyles" data-mw='{"name":"templatestyles","attrs":{"src":"Module:Citation/CS1/styles.css"},"body":{"extsrc":""}}' id="mwDKI"/></span></li><li about="#cite_note-WA-306" id="cite_note-WA-306"><a href="./Socialism#cite_ref-WA_306-0" rel="mw:referencedBy"><span class="mw-linkback-text">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-WA-306" class="mw-reference-text"><cite class="citation book" about="#mwt1339" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"cite book ","href":"./Template:Cite_book"},"params":{"last":{"wt":"Walicki"},"first":{"wt":"Andrzej"},"title":{"wt":"Marxism and the leap to the kingdom of freedom: the rise and fall of the Communist utopia"},"publisher":{"wt":"Stanford University Press"},"location":{"wt":"Stanford, Calif"},"year":{"wt":"1995"},"isbn":{"wt":"978-0-8047-2384-8"},"page":{"wt":"95"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwDKM">Walicki, Andrzej (1995). <i id="mwDKQ">Marxism and the leap to the kingdom of freedom: the rise and fall of the Communist utopia</i>. Stanford, Calif: Stanford University Press. p.<span typeof="mw:Entity" id="mwDKU"> </span>95. <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./International_Standard_Book_Number" title="International Standard Book Number" id="mwDKY">ISBN</a><span typeof="mw:Entity" id="mwDKc"> </span><a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Special:BookSources/978-0-8047-2384-8" title="Special:BookSources/978-0-8047-2384-8" id="mwDKg">978-0-8047-2384-8</a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Marxism+and+the+leap+to+the+kingdom+of+freedom%3A+the+rise+and+fall+of+the+Communist+utopia&amp;rft.place=Stanford%2C+Calif&amp;rft.pages=95&amp;rft.pub=Stanford+University+Press&amp;rft.date=1995&amp;rft.isbn=978-0-8047-2384-8&amp;rft.aulast=Walicki&amp;rft.aufirst=Andrzej&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ASocialism" class="Z3988" about="#mwt1339" id="mwDKk"></span><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r879151008" about="#mwt1339" typeof="mw:Extension/templatestyles" data-mw='{"name":"templatestyles","attrs":{"src":"Module:Citation/CS1/styles.css"},"body":{"extsrc":""}}' id="mwDKo"/></span></li><li about="#cite_note-FOOTNOTEBerlau194921-307" id="cite_note-FOOTNOTEBerlau194921-307"><a href="./Socialism#cite_ref-FOOTNOTEBerlau194921_307-0" rel="mw:referencedBy"><span class="mw-linkback-text">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-FOOTNOTEBerlau194921-307" class="mw-reference-text"><a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Socialism#CITEREFBerlau1949" id="mwDKs">Berlau 1949</a>, p.<span typeof="mw:Entity" id="mwDKw"> </span>21.</span></li><li about="#cite_note-308" id="cite_note-308"><a href="./Socialism#cite_ref-308" rel="mw:referencedBy"><span class="mw-linkback-text">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-308" class="mw-reference-text"><cite id="p._295" class="citation book" about="#mwt1344" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"cite book ","href":"./Template:Cite_book"},"params":{"last":{"wt":"Screpanti and Zamagni"},"title":{"wt":"An Outline on the History of Economic Thought"},"edition":{"wt":"2nd"},"year":{"wt":"2005"},"publisher":{"wt":"Oxford"},"quote":{"wt":"It should not be forgotten, however, that in the period of the Second International, some of the reformist currents of Marxism, as well as some of the extreme left-wing ones, not to speak of the anarchist groups, had already criticised the view that State ownership and central planning is the best road to socialism. But with the victory of Leninism in Russia, all dissent was silenced, and socialism became identified with ‘democratic centralism’, ‘central planning’, and State ownership of the means of production."},"ref":{"wt":"p. 295"}},"i":0}}]}'>Screpanti and Zamagni (2005). <i id="mwDK0">An Outline on the History of Economic Thought</i> (2nd ed.). Oxford. <q id="mwDK4">It should not be forgotten, however, that in the period of the Second International, some of the reformist currents of Marxism, as well as some of the extreme left-wing ones, not to speak of the anarchist groups, had already criticised the view that State ownership and central planning is the best road to socialism. But with the victory of Leninism in Russia, all dissent was silenced, and socialism became identified with ‘democratic centralism’, ‘central planning’, and State ownership of the means of production.</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=An+Outline+on+the+History+of+Economic+Thought&amp;rft.edition=2nd&amp;rft.pub=Oxford&amp;rft.date=2005&amp;rft.au=Screpanti+and+Zamagni&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ASocialism" class="Z3988" about="#mwt1344" id="mwDK8"></span><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r879151008" about="#mwt1344" typeof="mw:Extension/templatestyles" data-mw='{"name":"templatestyles","attrs":{"src":"Module:Citation/CS1/styles.css"},"body":{"extsrc":""}}' id="mwDLA"/></span></li><li about="#cite_note-309" id="cite_note-309"><a href="./Socialism#cite_ref-309" rel="mw:referencedBy"><span class="mw-linkback-text">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-309" class="mw-reference-text"><cite class="citation book" about="#mwt1346" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"cite book ","href":"./Template:Cite_book"},"params":{"last":{"wt":"Schumpeter"},"first":{"wt":"Joseph"},"title":{"wt":"Capitalism, Socialism and Democracy"},"publisher":{"wt":"Harper Perennial"},"date":{"wt":"2008"},"isbn":{"wt":"978-0-06-156161-0"},"page":{"wt":"169"},"quote":{"wt":"But there are still others (concepts and institutions) which by virtue of their nature cannot stand transplantation and always carry the flavor of a particular institutional framework. It is extremely dangerous, in fact it amounts to a distortion of historical description, to use them beyond the social world or culture whose denizens they are. Now ownership or property—also, so I believe, taxation—are such denizens of the world of commercial society, exactly as knights and fiefs are denizens of the feudal world. But so is the state (a denizen of commercial society)."}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwDLE">Schumpeter, Joseph (2008). <i id="mwDLI">Capitalism, Socialism and Democracy</i>. Harper Perennial. p.<span typeof="mw:Entity" id="mwDLM"> </span>169. <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./International_Standard_Book_Number" title="International Standard Book Number" id="mwDLQ">ISBN</a><span typeof="mw:Entity" id="mwDLU"> </span><a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Special:BookSources/978-0-06-156161-0" title="Special:BookSources/978-0-06-156161-0" id="mwDLY">978-0-06-156161-0</a>. <q id="mwDLc">But there are still others (concepts and institutions) which by virtue of their nature cannot stand transplantation and always carry the flavor of a particular institutional framework. It is extremely dangerous, in fact it amounts to a distortion of historical description, to use them beyond the social world or culture whose denizens they are. Now ownership or property—also, so I believe, taxation—are such denizens of the world of commercial society, exactly as knights and fiefs are denizens of the feudal world. But so is the state (a denizen of commercial society).</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Capitalism%2C+Socialism+and+Democracy&amp;rft.pages=169&amp;rft.pub=Harper+Perennial&amp;rft.date=2008&amp;rft.isbn=978-0-06-156161-0&amp;rft.aulast=Schumpeter&amp;rft.aufirst=Joseph&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ASocialism" class="Z3988" about="#mwt1346" id="mwDLg"></span><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r879151008" about="#mwt1346" typeof="mw:Extension/templatestyles" data-mw='{"name":"templatestyles","attrs":{"src":"Module:Citation/CS1/styles.css"},"body":{"extsrc":""}}' id="mwDLk"/></span></li><li about="#cite_note-310" id="cite_note-310"><a href="./Socialism#cite_ref-310" rel="mw:referencedBy"><span class="mw-linkback-text">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-310" class="mw-reference-text"><cite class="citation web" about="#mwt1351" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"cite web ","href":"./Template:Cite_web"},"params":{"url":{"wt":"https://www.pbs.org/heavenonearth/synopsis.html"},"title":{"wt":"Heaven on Earth: The Rise and Fall of Socialism"},"publisher":{"wt":"Public Broadcasting System"},"accessdate":{"wt":"15 December 2011"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwDLo"><a rel="mw:ExtLink" class="external text" href="https://www.pbs.org/heavenonearth/synopsis.html" id="mwDLs">"Heaven on Earth: The Rise and Fall of Socialism"</a>. Public Broadcasting System<span class="reference-accessdate" id="mwDLw">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap" id="mwDL0">15 December</span> 2011</span>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=Heaven+on+Earth%3A+The+Rise+and+Fall+of+Socialism&amp;rft.pub=Public+Broadcasting+System&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pbs.org%2Fheavenon